The paper proposes a new image representation for texture categorization and facial analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of mixture models and Fisher scores, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of classifiers and metrics, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
